With poor recruiting being one of the issues that led to the firing of Willingham6, Weis was challenged to coach the Patriots' offense during the day and work on recruiting players for the Irish at night.7 He took a proactive role in recruiting, including sending seven of his assistant coaches to a recruit who had de-committed after Willingham was fired8 (the recruit, however, signed with the 

Ohio State Buckeyes
). Weis, with some of Willingham's recruits signing also, built a class of 15 recruits, including five four star recruits.
